18,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3185018,"For Sale/Trade:  > > > Harley Heritage Springer 1,300 miles show condition! ! ! ! ! ! !","Smithfield, NC, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina","$ 15,500","Listed On: Tuesday, June 17, 2014",Vehicles,no type,no type,no type,no type,"http://raleigh.craigslist.org/mcy/REDACTED.html
Link above to the Craigslist listing with pics.
Truly a collectors dream !!! This bike is a time capsule !!! You would search the rest of your life and not find another 1997 OLD BOY with 1,300 original miles!
1997 Harley Davidson Heritage Springer FLSTS
1,300 miles. That is NOT a misprint.
One thousand three hundred miles.
This bike should be shown and will win every show it’s entered in. How often do you see an all original 17 year old bike with 1,300 miles?
Fresh full synthetic oil.
New Harley battery
This bike was owned by a 74 year old gentleman that didn’t ride it, obviously.

I sold my cuddy cabin boat to buy a walk around or a center console, but when I saw this bike, I just had to have it !!! So I bought it. I miss boating too much to keep this classic and I can’t afford both, so it’s for sale.
I’m not desperate, I will keep it if I don’t get enough cash or a boat of equal value, or a less expensive boat and some cash.

I might even trade for an every day rider, Harley only, and some cash to buy a small center console boat to cure my itch for the water. My 2003 harley Ultra has 65,000 miles and I usually keep a 2nd bike in the garage to ride, but I feel guilty putting miles on this rare gem. So, I could use another daily rider.
I’ve put some miles on the bike and it runs great and is an attention magnet !!! And I’ll continue to ride it a little until it’s gone.

Everybody loves it, it’s so classic and stylish. The history of the 1997 Heritage Springer is that it was designed after the 1948 Panhead. Those in the bike world refer to this as the “Old Boy”, again, after the ’48 Panhead.
If I keep it I’m getting that put on a vanity plate,,,”OLD BOY” !!!

Please don’t waste my time or yours with idiotic offers, price is FIRM !!!  It’s a 17 year old brand new bike. Go find another with 1,300 miles and in this condition. Oh wait, you won’t find one I’m sure. One thing is for sure, the value of this bike will only go up, never down. If you buy a brand new 2014 Heritage today, 5 years from now it’s worth $12,000.00?
What will this be worth in 5 years, over $20,000.00 for sure.
NO RIDES WITHOUT ALL THE CASH IN MY HAND !
Will also trade for Leer jet. Will need flying lessons."

The following description is critical and may make it sound to be in worse condition than it actuality is, but I would rather a buyer be pleasantly surprised than upset. This rifle was owned by one family for the last 50 years. The grandfather bought it, his son and two grandsons used it for 40 years. They shot it, carried it, stored it and hunted with it regularly.  For the last 10 years it has sat in the back of a closet until I bought it.

The receiver is not grooved for a scope. There has not been any after market modifications to this rifle! Many of the screws appear to have turned several times. The tube magazine is worn shinny with the use of the pump. The receiver is developing a patina in some places. The bluing is generally in good condition.

The wood is in good condition though it shows signs of significant use over the years. It appears there are finger ring marks at the grip, and the finish is mostly worn on the stock within an inch or two from the butt plate. There are no deep gouges or cracks in the wood. There are no cracks, chips, or other bad wood marks.

The pump action functions smoothly. The internals of this rifle are in excellent condition.  The trigger pull weight is 4 lbs. The safety functions properly. The bore appears bright. The rear sight may not have been adjusted in the last 40+ years! This rifle is a classic shooter.

I think the overall condition of this rifle is about 80%. That is the basis for cash price. I'm reasonable, but I'm not giving it away. I prefer FTF in Aiken, but if you pay all shipping, I will ship it to your FFL. USPS Money Order will be required for long distance transaction.

700,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3185700,For Sale:  Chinese Type 56 SKS - Matching Numbers,"Conway/OIA, Orlando, Florida",$ 330,"Listed On: Tuesday, June 17, 2014",Rifles,no type,7.62x39                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"For sale is a Chinese Type 56 SKS made in 1958 at Factory 26 with all matching numbers (receiver, botlt, bolt carrier, magazine, trigger guard, gas tube, and stock).  This being an early Chinese SKS it is of all milled construction, even the gas piston tube is milled, not stamped.  Also features a chrome lined barrel and chamber that looks nearly brand new.  The stock has no cracks and a nice grain pattern but as you can see it has definitely been there and done that.  The story that I heard for this batch of rifles is that they made their way from China to Yugoslavia/Bosnia and used there during the early 90s.  An individual even carved their name into the stock, it looks like the name ""Zerpiun"" or something similar, so it has some real deal trench art.  Bluing is around 60% (conservative estimate), but there is no rust anywhere.  Selling to make more room in my safe, plus I already have a few AKs so this gun doesn't see much use.  When I received the gun the sear had a negative engagement with the hammer causing a potentially unsafe condition, which is a common issue with these guns.  The sear has been recut to provide safe function.
Rifle comes with sling, cleaning kit, and 20 brand new stripper clips.  Must be 18, have a FL Driver's License and/or FL CWP and sign a Bill of Sale.
Please see the following link for more detailed pictures: http://imgur.com/a/FUUds"
